<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Slam &lt; stun kick and all warriors get that at 55th.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's not true.  Bash (slam) caps at 240, kick caps at 210.  You'll land slam more frequently than you land kick.  Who cares if you do 15 more damage on average with kick?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   In the high end game, all races are equally good. Just get your stam max'd get htp gear, have good ac.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Ogres are nice that they dont stun from the front and yes id agree a minor amount of agro is lost during a stun. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
All races are not equally good.  There are racial benefits, the biggest is by far Ogre FSI (frontal stun immunity -- and yes, other races have benefits too), this increases avoidance by a ton on fast hitting MOBs (you cannot riposte, dodge, parry while stunned, and MOBs like Vindicator or Tormax will stun -a lot- if you are not an ogre).  The point of FSI is NOT that you lose aggro, it's that you avoid more damage...  Does it mean non-Ogres can't tank? Not at all...CH rotation will never rely on such a small margin for it to really matter.<br>
<br>
Other than stamina, the other combat stats are stupidly easy to max out so it doesn't really matter.  If you're not at that point yet, I guess strength would be good (more ATK = more taunt), but really I can't imagine this being crucial when you can't max out strength.  Agi and dex are just about worthless regardless.  Stamina is a bit harder to raise, 205 is generally what you aim for (SHM buff is 50), but most high-end tanks get to 255 unbuffed to save a buff slot (yes that's important). <p>--Lacus<br>Grandmaster<br>
